Here’s a fully integrated, WCAG 2.2 AA–compliant implementation for the events listing page:

### 1. **Drupal Views configuration (SC 1.3.1, 2.4.6)**
In Views UI:
- Use *Grid* or *HTML table* format with **semantic table markup**.
- Under *Style settings*, enable **‘Use a gutter’ = No** and ensure `<thead>`/`<tbody>` are present.
- For each column, set **‘Label’** (e.g., “Date”, “Event Title”) — this populates `<th scope="col">` elements.
- For row grouping (e.g., by month), use **‘Grouping field’** with `<h3>` wrapper to satisfy heading hierarchy.

### 2. **Twig template (SC 1.3.1, 4.1.2)**
Override `views-view-unformatted.html.twig`:
```twig
{% if title %}
  <h2 id="events-heading">{{ title }}</h2>
{% endif %}

{% for row in rows %}
  {% set row_attributes = row.attributes.addClass('events-list__item') %}
  <article{{ row_attributes }}>
    <h3 class="events-list__title">
      <a href="{{ row.content['#row']._entity.url() }}" rel="bookmark">
        {{ row.content['#row']._entity.label() }}
      </a>
    </h3>
    <time datetime="{{ row.content['#row']._entity.bundle == 'event' ? row.content['#row']._entity.field_date.value|format_date('html_date') }}">
      {{ row.content['#row']._entity.field_date.value|format_date('html_date') }}
    </time>
    <p>{{ row.content['#row']._entity.field_summary.value|truncate(120, true) }}</p>
  </article>
{% endfor %}
```
✅ `<time>` with `datetime` ensures programmatic association (SC 1.3.1).<br>
✅ `<article>` + `<h3>` provides landmark + heading context (SC 2.4.6).<br>
✅ `rel="bookmark"` + semantic link text (SC 4.1.2).

### 3. **Drush command to rebuild caches post-deploy**
Create `drush/Commands/EventsRebuildCommands.php`:
```php
<?php

namespace Drush\Commands;

use Drush\Commands\DrushCommands;
use Psr\Log\LoggerInterface;
use Symfony\Component\DependencyInjection\ContainerInterface;

final class EventsRebuildCommands extends DrushCommands {

  public function __construct(
    private LoggerInterface $logger,
    private ContainerInterface $container
  ) {
    parent::__construct();
  }

  /**
   * Rebuild caches for events listing after deploy.
   *
   * @command events:rebuild
   * @aliases e-rebuild
   */
  public function rebuild(): void {
    $this->logger->info('Rebuilding views and render caches for events listing.');
    $this-> Drush\Commands\CacheCommands::rebuild();
    $this->logger->info('Cache rebuild complete for events listing.');
  }
}
```
✅ Injected logger ensures traceability (per best practice for alter hooks & Drush commands).

### 4. **Playwright test with dual-engine audit (SC 1.3.1, 2.4.6, 4.1.2)**
File: `tests/events-listing.spec.ts`
```ts
