To meet WCAG 2.2 AA compliance for the event listing page:

### 1. **Views table configuration (SC 1.3.1, 2.4.6)**
Use `table` style in Views and define explicit `<caption>` and `<thead>` with `<th>` headers for each column (e.g., Title, Date, Location). Ensure `scope="col"` is set automatically.

Example config (YAML snippet for `views.view.events.yml`):
```yaml
display:
  default:
    display_options:
      table_options:
        info:
          -
            column: title
            sortable: true
            default_sort_order: asc
            header: Event
            separator: ''
          -
            column: field_date
            header: Date
          -
            column: field_location
            header: Location
```

### 2. **Twig template with accessible calendar buttons (SC 2.4.6, 4.1.2)**
In `views-view-fields--events.html.twig`, render calendar links with explicit labels:
```twig
{# Do NOT use icon-only buttons #}
<a href="{{ calendar_url }}" class="btn btn-calendar" aria-label="Add {{ title }} to Google Calendar">
  <span class="visually-hidden">Add to Calendar</span>
  <svg aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><!-- calendar icon --></svg>
</a>
```

Avoid icons-only: SC 2.4.6 requires sufficient contrast *and* meaningful labels. If icons must be used, pair them with visible, high-contrast text or ARIA labels.

