Here’s a full-stack accessible block implementation for critical announcements:

**1. Block Plugin (PHP, SC 1.4.1, SC 2.4.7, SC 4.1.2)**

`modules/custom/announcements/src/Plugin/Block/AlertBlock.php`:
```php
<?php

namespace Drupal\announcements\Plugin\Block;

use Drupal\block\BlockBase;
use Drupal\core\form\FormStateInterface;
use Drupal\core\plugin\BlockBase;

/**
 * Provides an accessible alert block for critical announcements.
 *
 * @Block(
 *   id = "announcements_alert_block",
 *   admin_label = @Translation("Accessible Alert Block"),
 *   category = @Translation("Announcements"),
 * )
 */
class AlertBlock extends BlockBase {

  public function defaultConfiguration() {
    return parent::defaultConfiguration() + [
      'alert_level' => 'warning',
      'title' => '',
      'message' => '',
    ];
  }

  public function blockForm($form, FormStateInterface $form_state) {
    $form['alert_level'] = [
      '#type' => 'select',
      '#title' => $this->t('Alert Level'),
      '#options' => [
        'info' => $this->t('Informational'),
        'warning' => $this->t('Warning'),
        'critical' => $this->t('Critical'),
      ],
      '#default_value' => $this->configuration['alert_level'],
    ];

    $form['title'] = [
      '#type' => 'textfield',
      '#title' => $this->t('Headline'),
      '#default_value' => $this->configuration['title'],
      '#required' => TRUE,
    ];

    $form['message'] = [
      '#type' => 'textarea',
      '#title' => $this->t('Message'),
      '#default_value' => $this->configuration['message'],
      '#required' => TRUE,
    ];

    return $form;
  }

  public function build() {
    $level = $this->configuration['alert_level'];
    $colors = [
      'info' => ['#0056b3', '#ffffff'],
      'warning' => ['#ffc107', '#212529'],
      'critical' => ['#dc3545', '#ffffff'],
    ];
    [$bg, $fg] = $colors[$level];

    return [
      '#theme' => 'announcements_alert_block',
      '#attributes' => [
        'role' => 'alert',
        'aria-live' => 'assertive',
        'style' => "background-color:{$bg}; color:{$fg}; border-left: 4px solid {$fg};",
      ],
      'title' => [
        '#markup' => '<h2>' . Html::escape($this->configuration['title']) . '</h2>',
      ],
      'message' => [
        '#markup' => '<p>' . Html::escape($this->configuration['message']) . '</p>',
      ],
      '#cache' => ['max-age' => 0],
    ];
  }
}
```
→ SC 2.4.7 (Focus Visible): block uses `role="alert"` for immediate screen reader announcement.
→ SC 4.1.2 (Name, Role, Value): `role="alert"`, `aria-live="assertive"`.
→ SC 1.4.1 (Use of Color): color contrast is controlled via CSS (not just color), and contrast validated below.

**2. Twig Template (SC 1.4.11, SC 1.4.1)**

`modules/custom/announcements/templates/announcements-alert-block.html.twig`:
```twig
