### 3. Drush Command: Batch Legacy Content Migration + Cache Rebuild
`src/Drush/Commands/PressReleaseMigrateCommands.php`:
```php
use Drush\Commands\DrushCommands;
use Drupal\node\Entity\Node;

/**
 * @command press-release:migrate
 * @description Migrate legacy press release nodes to new structure.
 */
class PressReleaseMigrateCommands extends DrushCommands {

  public function migrate() {
    $query = \Drupal::entityQuery('node')
      ->condition('type', 'legacy_press')
      ->range(0, 50);
    $nids = $query->execute();

    foreach (Node::loadMultiple($nids) as $node) {
      $new_node = Node::create([
        'type' => 'press_release',
        'title' => $node->get('title')->value,
        'field_release_date' => $node->get('created')->value,
        'body' => $node->get('body')->value,
      ]);
      $new_node->save();

      // Mark old node as deprecated
      $node->set('status', FALSE);
      $node->save();
    }

    drush_log(dt('Migrated @count nodes to press_release type.', ['@count' => count($nids)]), 'ok');

    // Rebuild caches + views
    $this->output()->writeln('<comment>Rebuilding caches…</comment>');
    drush_drush_shell_output('drush cr');
    drush_drush_shell_output('drush views:rebuild');
  }
}
```

Usage:
```bash
drush press-release:migrate
# → Migrates 50 nodes at a time (batchable), rebuilds caches
```

