### 3. Drush Command to Import Legacy Events (SC 1.3.1, 1.4.1)
**File:** `src/Commands/EventImportCommands.php`
```php
<?php

namespace Drupal\event_calendar_acess\Commands;

use Drush\Commands\DrushCommands;
use DateTime;

class EventImportCommands extends DrushCommands {

  /**
   * Import legacy events from CSV.
   *
   * @command event:import
   * @aliases event-import
   */
  public function import(): void {
    $file = 'legacy_events.csv';
    $handle = fopen($file, 'r');
    $header = fgetcsv($handle);

    while (($data = fgetcsv($handle)) !== FALSE) {
      list($title, $date, $location) = $data;

      // Validate date (SC 1.4.1 — avoid ambiguous formats)
      $dt = DateTime::createFromFormat('Y-m-d', trim($date));
      if (!$dt || $dt->format('Y-m-d') !== trim($date)) {
        $this->logger()->warning("Invalid date: {$date}");
        continue;
      }

      // Create node
      $node = \Drupal\node\Entity\Node::create([
        'type' => 'event',
        'title' => trim($title),
        'field_event_date' => $dt->getTimestamp(),
        'field_event_location' => trim($location),
      ]);
      $node->save();
    }

    fclose($handle);
    $this->logger()->success('Imported events successfully.');
  }
}
```

Run:
```bash
vendor/bin/drush event:import
```

- Validates date format to prevent misordered day/month (SC 1.4.1 — meaningful sequence)

