### 3. **Drush Command for Daily Cache Warmup (SC 2.4.4, 4.1.1)**
Create `src/Drush/Commands/EventsCacheCommand.php`:
```php
<?php

namespace Drupal\my_module\Drush\Commands;

use Drush\Attributes as CLI;
use Drush\Commands\DrushCommands;

final class EventsCacheCommand extends DrushCommands {

  #[CLI\Command(name: 'my-module:events-cache:warmup')]
  public function warmup(): void {
    $this->logger()->notice('Warming up events cache…');
    $ids = \Drupal::entityTypeManager()
      ->getStorage('node')
      ->getQuery()
      ->accessCheck(FALSE)
      ->condition('type', 'event')
      ->condition('status', 1)
      ->range(0, 500)
      ->execute();
    foreach (array_chunk($ids, 100) as $chunk) {
      $nodes = \Drupal::entityTypeManager()->getStorage('node')->loadMultiple($chunk);
      foreach ($nodes as $node) {
        \Drupal::service('router.route_provider')->getRoutesByNames(['entity.node.canonical'], $node)->count();
      }
    }
    \Drupal::service('page_cache_kill_switch')->trigger();
    $this->logger()->notice('Events cache warmed up.');
  }
}
```
- Runs nightly via cron to avoid latency spikes (SC 2.4.4: Link Purpose)
