### 2. Accessible Block Plugin with Configurable Filters (PHP)

**`src/Plugin/Block/AccessibleEventBlock.php`:**
```php
namespace Drupal\my_events\Plugin\Block;

use Drupal\block\BlockBase;
use Drupal\Core\Form\FormStateInterface;

/**
 * Provides an accessible event listing block.
 *
 * @Block(
 *   id = "accessible_event_block",
 *   admin_label = @Translation("Accessible Event Listing"),
 *   category = @Translation("Custom"),
 * )
 */
class AccessibleEventBlock extends BlockBase {

  public function defaultConfiguration() {
    return parent::defaultConfiguration() + [
      'max_events' => 5,
    ];
  }

  public function blockForm($form, FormStateInterface $form_state) {
    $form['max_events'] = [
      '#type' => 'number',
      '#title' => $this->t('Maximum events to show'),
      '#default_value' => $this->configuration['max_events'],
      '#min' => 1,
    ];
    return $form;
  }

  public function blockSubmit($form, FormStateInterface $form_state) {
    $this->configuration['max_events'] = $form_state->getValue('max_events');
  }

  public function build() {
    $events = $this->getEvents(limit: $this->configuration['max_events']);

    $build = [
      '#theme' => 'my_events_list',
      '#events' => $events,
      '#cache' => ['max-age' => 3600],
    ];

    // Ensure proper ARIA landmark
    $build['#attributes'] = [
      'role' => 'region',
      'aria-label' => $this->t('Upcoming events'),
    ];

    return $build;
  }

  protected function getEvents(int $limit = 5): array {
    $query = \Drupal::entityTypeManager()
      ->getStorage('node')
      ->getQuery()
      ->accessCheck(TRUE)
      ->condition('type', 'event')
      ->condition('status', 1)
      ->sort('field_event_date', 'DESC')
      ->range(0, $limit);

    $nids = $query->execute();
    return \Drupal\node\Entity\Node::loadMultiple($nids);
  }

}
```

### 3. Twig Template with Semantic HTML & ARIA (`.html.twig`)

**`templates/my-events-list.html.twig`:**
```twig
{#
/**
 * @file
 * Theme implementation for accessible event listing.
 *
 * Variables:
 * - events: Array of node entities.
 */
#}

{% if events %}
  <ul{{ attributes.addClass('events-list') }}>
    {% for event in events %}
      <li class="events-list__item">
        <h3 class="events-list__title">
          <a href="{{ path('entity.node.canonical', {'node': event.id}) }}"
             rel="bookmark"
             class="events-list__link">
            {{ event.title.value }}
          </a>
        </h3>
        <time datetime="{{ event.field_event_date.value|date('c') }}"
              class="events-list__date">
          {{ event.field_event_date.value|date('F j, Y') }}
        </time>
        {% if event.field_event_location %}
          <p class="events-list__location">
            {{ event.field_event_location.value }}
          </p>
        {% endif %}
      </li>
    {% endfor %}
  </ul>
{% else %}
  <p>{{ 'No upcoming events.'|t }}</p>
{% endif %}
```

**Key accessibility features:**
- Semantic `<ul>`/`<li>` → SC 1.3.1 (Info & Relationships)
- `aria-label` on region → SC 1.3.1 (Landmark labeling)
- `<time>` element with ISO date → SC 1.3.1 (Structure & machine-readable date)
- `href` on `<a>` → SC 2.1.1 (Keyboard), SC 4.1.2 (Name, Role, Value)

