Here’s a complete e2e solution for SC 3.1.1 (Language of Page) and SC 2.4.7 (Focus Visible):

### 1. **Drush Command: `twig:audit`** (`src/Drush/Commands/TwigAuditCommands.php`)

```php
<?php

namespace Drupal\my_module\Drush\Commands;

use Drush\Attributes as CLI;
use Drush\Commands\DrushCommands;
use Twig\Environment;
use Twig\Loader\FilesystemLoader;

#[CLI\Command(name: 'twig:audit', aliases: ['twig-audit'])]
#[CLI\Option(name: 'output', description: 'Output format: table, json, csv')]
#[CLI\Usage(name: 'drush twig:audit --output=json', description: 'Audit all Twig templates for lang/aria attributes')]
class TwigAuditCommands extends DrushCommands {

  private Environment $twig;

  public function __construct() {
    $loader = new FilesystemLoader([
      drupal_get_path('module', 'my_module') . '/templates',
      drupal_get_path('theme', 'my_theme') . '/templates',
    ]);
    $this->twig = new Environment($loader, [
      'debug' => TRUE,
      'cache' => FALSE,
    ]);
  }

  public function audit($options = ['output' => 'table']): void {
    $violations = [];

    foreach ($this->twig->getLoader()->getCacheKey('page.html.twig') as $template) {
      try {
        $source = $this->twig->getLoader()->getSourceContext($template)->getCode();
        if (!str_contains($source, 'lang="{{ language.langcode }}"')) {
          $violations[] = [
            'template' => $template,
            'issue' => 'Missing `lang` attribute on <html> tag',
            'sc' => '3.1.1',
          ];
        }
        if (!str_contains($source, 'class="focus-visible"') && !str_contains($source, 'inset: 2px solid transparent')) {
          $violations[] = [
            'template' => $template,
            'issue' => 'No visible focus indicator defined',
            'sc' => '2.4.7',
          ];
        }
      } catch (\Throwable $e) {
        // Log debug
      }
    }

    $this->io()->table(
      ['Template', 'Issue', 'SC'],
      array_map(fn($v) => [$v['template'], $v['issue'], $v['sc']], $violations)
    );

    if (count($violations) === 0) {
      $this->output()->writeln('<info>No violations found for SC 3.1.1 or SC 2.4.7.</info>');
    }
  }
}
```

### 2. **Twig Template Snippet** (`page.html.twig`)
```twig
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html{{ html_attributes }} lang="{{ language.langcode }}">
<head>
  <style>
    .focus-visible:focus {
      outline: 2px solid #0085ba;
      outline-offset: 2px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body{{ body_attributes }}>
  {{ page }}
</body>
</html>
```

### 3. **Playwright Accessibility Test**
```ts
// e2e/lang-focus.spec.ts
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';
import { AxeBuilder } from '@axe-core/playwright';

test('SC 3.1.1 and SC 2.4.7 compliance', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto('https://agency.example.org');

  // SC 3.1.1: html[lang] must be present and valid
  const html = page.locator('html');
  await expect(html).toHaveAttribute('lang', /^[a-z]{2}(-[A-Z]{2})?$/);

  // SC 2.4.7: All focusable elements must have visible focus
  const results = await new AxeBuilder({ page })
    .withTags(['wcag2a', 'wcag21aa', 'wcag22aa'])
    .include('body')
    .exclude('[aria-hidden="true"]')
    .analyze();

  const focusViolations = results.violations.filter(
    v => v.id === 'focus-visible'
  );

  expect(focusViolations).toHaveLength(0);
});
```

### 4. **Integration Workflow**
1. Run `drush twig:audit --output=json > audit.json`
2. Fix templates per report
3. Commit changes
4. Deploy with `drush deploy`
5. Run `npm run test:e2e:accessibility`

✅ **SC Summary**
- **SC 3.1.1**: `html[lang]` present and machine-readable
- **SC 2.4.7**: No invisible focus indicators (e.g., `outline: none` without replacement)

